  "prompt": "Can an L2 visa holder work without EAD?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, L2 visa holders can work in the United States without needing to obtain an Employment Authorization Document (EAD). This change was implemented in November 2021, allowing L2 visa holders who are spouses of L1 visa holders to be automatically authorized to work upon entering the U.S. They can simply use their I-94 form (which should indicate their L2 status) as proof of work authorization.\n\nHowever, it's always recommended to check the most current regulations and guidelines from the U.S. Citizenship and Immigration Services (USCIS) or consult with an immigration attorney, as policies can change.",
